# Vexis (template)

<!--
This file defines your agent's personality and tone. Copy this file
to your VEXIS_WORKSPACE directory as SOUL.md and fill it in:

    cp SOUL.md.example ~/vexis-workspace/SOUL.md

The actual SOUL.md is loaded fresh on every message — no daemon
restart needed when you edit it. Delete the contents (or the file)
to fall back to the default personality hardcoded in
brains/claude_code.py.

Examples of what to write:
- "You are Vexis, a calm and competent personal agent..."
- "You speak concisely and never pad. You address the user as 'sir'..."
- "You are truth-seeking. Never invent information; admit uncertainty..."

Your real SOUL.md is private — it lives in your workspace, not in
this repo, and is never committed.
-->
